dsDescriptionValue.value:
These dataset are the Replication Data for  A degree-based block model and a local expansion optimization algorithm for anti-community detection in networks, which is published in PLOS ONE with DOI: 10.1371/journal.pone.0195226.
These dataset included synthetic and real-world networks, executable codes for benchmark DBM-Net, and proposed algorithms LEOA.

publicationCitation.value: J. Zhu, Y. Liu, C. Yang, et al. A degree-based block model and a local expansion optimization algorithm for anti-community detection in networks. PLOS ONE, 13(4): e0195226
1. Newman MEJ. Finding community structure in networks using the eigenvectors of matrices. Phys Rev E. 2006; 74(3): 036104. DOI: 10.1103/PhysRevE.74.036104

fields.value: These dataset include synthetic networks DBM-Net, 17 real-world networks for evaluation, executable codes for benchmark DBM-Net and proposed algorithms LEOA. Particularly,real-world networks are divided into two categories: disassortative network and assortative network. The first 6 networks are disassortative networks and the last 11 networks are assortative networks.
